    Chapter: 43
Title: Water and Stone
---
What’s softest in the world
rushes and runs
over what’s hardest in the world.

The immaterial
enters
the impenetrable.

So I know the good in not doing.
The wordless teaching,
the profit in not doing --
not many people understand it.
